---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  lang="en"
  title="DBS | YWAM Sendai"
  description="Discipleship Bible School (DBS) at YWAM Sendai is a 12-week YWAM school focused on deep engagement with Scripture through whole-Bible reading, chronological study, and faithful interpretation."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container hero-inner">
      <div class="stack">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Discipleship Bible School</p>
          <h1 class="hero-title max-w-title">
            A focused season of deep engagement with Scripture.
          </h1>
        </div>

        <p class="lead">
          DBS at YWAM Sendai is a 12-week school designed to help students know
          God through His Word, strengthen their biblical foundation, and grow
          in faithful interpretation and application of Scripture.
        </p>

        <div class="btn-group">
          <button type="button" class="btn-primary open-hub-trigger">Ask AI</button>
          <a href="/en/apply" class="btn-secondary-dark">Apply</a>
          <a
            href="https://guide.ywamsendai.org/en"
            class="btn-secondary-dark"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            Visit Handbook
          </a>
        </div>

        <p class="text-inverse-soft mb-0">
          Ask about DBS, prerequisites, study rhythm, dates, or whether this school may be a good fit.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card hero-feature-card stack-sm">
        <p class="eyebrow">Quick Overview</p>
        <h2 class="card-title">What DBS is</h2>
        <p>
          DBS is a Bible-focused YWAM school in which students read through the
          entire Bible chronologically and study Scripture as one unified story
          of God’s redemptive purposes.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-paper">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid-4">
        <article class="card">
          <h2 class="card-title">Length</h2>
          <p>12 weeks</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <h2 class="card-title">Focus</h2>
          <p>Whole-Bible reading and biblical interpretation</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <h2 class="card-title">Study Method</h2>
          <p>Chronological, immersive, and discussion-based</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card surface-accent-soft">
          <h2 class="card-title">Prerequisite</h2>
          <p>Completion of DTS is required</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-intro container-narrow">
        <p class="eyebrow">What is DBS?</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">
          A Bible school shaped by reading the whole story of Scripture.
        </h2>
        <p class="lead">
          DBS stands for Discipleship Bible School. It is a YWAM school focused
          on sustained reading, study, interpretation, and reflection so that
          students grow in biblical literacy, confidence, and faithfulness in handling the Word of God.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid-3">
        <article class="card card-interactive">
          <h3 class="card-title">Read the whole Bible</h3>
          <p>Students read through the entire Bible during the school.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card card-interactive">
          <h3 class="card-title">Follow the biblical storyline</h3>
          <p>Scripture is studied in chronological flow from Genesis to Revelation.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card card-interactive">
          <h3 class="card-title">Apply Scripture faithfully</h3>
          <p>Students learn to interpret carefully and connect biblical truth to life and ministry.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-paper">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid-2" style="align-items: start;">
        <div class="stack-sm">
          <p class="eyebrow">DBS at YWAM Sendai</p>
          <h2 class="section-title">Serious study within a discipleship and mission context</h2>
          <p class="lead">
            DBS at YWAM Sendai is not only academic. It takes place within the wider
            life of the base, where worship, prayer, humility, obedience, and community
            participation remain part of the learning environment.
          </p>
          <p class="text-soft">
            Students study Scripture deeply while also living in a context shaped by
            discipleship, mission awareness, and life in Sendai and the wider Tohoku region.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid stack-sm">
          <article class="card card-interactive">
            <h3 class="card-title">Worship and prayer</h3>
            <p>Bible study is held within rhythms of devotion and dependence on God.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="card card-interactive">
            <h3 class="card-title">Humility and obedience</h3>
            <p>Students are encouraged to approach Scripture with attentiveness and integrity.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="card card-interactive">
            <h3 class="card-title">Community participation</h3>
            <p>Learning happens through discussion, shared life, and mutual sharpening.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="card card-interactive">
            <h3 class="card-title">Mission awareness</h3>
            <p>The Bible is studied not only for knowledge, but for faithful life and ministry.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-intro container-narrow">
        <p class="eyebrow">Study Approach</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">How Scripture is studied in DBS</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          DBS at YWAM Sendai follows a chronological and immersive approach to Scripture,
          combining whole-Bible reading, classroom teaching, discussion, and reflection.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid-2">
        <article class="card">
          <span class="chip-accent">Practice</span>
          <h3 class="card-title">Core learning practices</h3>
          <ul class="list-clean">
            <li>Chronological study of the biblical storyline</li>
            <li>Reading through the entire Bible</li>
            <li>Inductive learning and careful observation</li>
            <li>Attention to historical setting and literary genre</li>
            <li>Small-group processing and discussion</li>
            <li>Written work and personal reflection</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <span class="chip-accent">Rhythm</span>
          <h3 class="card-title">What students should expect</h3>
          <ul class="list-clean">
            <li>Serious engagement with Scripture</li>
            <li>Regular reading and academic responsibility</li>
            <li>Thoughtful participation in class and discussion</li>
            <li>Community life and shared rhythms</li>
            <li>Spiritual formation alongside study</li>
            <li>Discipline, attentiveness, and perseverance</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-paper">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-intro container-narrow">
        <p class="eyebrow">Weekly Curriculum</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">A 12-week journey through the whole Bible</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          DBS follows a fixed weekly curriculum that helps students understand the flow
          of biblical history and the unity of God’s redemptive plan.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid-2">
        <article class="card card-interactive">
          <span class="chip-accent">Weeks 1–4</span>
          <ul class="list-clean">
            <li><strong>Week 1:</strong> Worldview and Origins</li>
            <li><strong>Week 2:</strong> Pentateuch</li>
            <li><strong>Week 3:</strong> Tribal History</li>
            <li><strong>Week 4:</strong> The Kingdom of David</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="card card-interactive">
          <span class="chip-accent">Weeks 5–8</span>
          <ul class="list-clean">
            <li><strong>Week 5:</strong> The Kings of Israel and Judah</li>
            <li><strong>Week 6:</strong> The Early Prophets</li>
            <li><strong>Week 7:</strong> The Late Prophets and Exile</li>
            <li><strong>Week 8:</strong> Post-Exilic and Inter-Testament</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="card card-interactive">
          <span class="chip-accent">Weeks 9–10</span>
          <ul class="list-clean">
            <li><strong>Week 9:</strong> The Life of Jesus</li>
            <li><strong>Week 10:</strong> The Early Church</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="card card-interactive">
          <span class="chip-accent">Weeks 11–12</span>
          <ul class="list-clean">
            <li><strong>Week 11:</strong> The Pauline Epistles</li>
            <li><strong>Week 12:</strong> The Johannine Writings</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>

      <div class="container-narrow" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
        <p class="text-soft">
          Specific books, themes, and teaching emphasis are organized within this fixed structure.
          Full curriculum details can be provided separately as planning is finalized.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-intro container-narrow">
        <p class="eyebrow">Who is DBS for?</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">For those who want to be grounded more deeply in Scripture</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          DBS is for students who want to deepen their understanding of the Bible,
          strengthen their biblical foundation, and be formed by God’s Word in a focused community setting.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid-3">
        <article class="card-dark">
          <h3 class="card-title">Deepen biblical understanding</h3>
          <p>For those who want a stronger grasp of the whole Bible and its unified story.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card-dark">
          <h3 class="card-title">Grow in disciplined study</h3>
          <p>For those ready for sustained reading, reflection, and careful interpretation.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card-dark">
          <h3 class="card-title">Prepare for what’s next</h3>
          <p>For those preparing for ministry, leadership, or further training rooted in Scripture.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-paper border-top">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-intro container-narrow">
        <p class="eyebrow">Dates and Costs</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Current planning information for DBS</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          DBS is currently in the planning phase. Specific dates will be confirmed later,
          but the following information provides a general picture for preparation.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid-2" style="align-items: start;">
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Dates</h3>
          <div class="stack-sm">
            <div>
              <p class="eyebrow">Anticipated Start</p>
              <p>April 2027</p>
            </div>
            <div class="surface-accent rounded-md p-lg">
              <p class="eyebrow">Status</p>
              <p><strong>Planning phase</strong></p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="eyebrow">Duration</p>
              <p>12 weeks</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Estimated Costs</h3>
          <div class="stack-sm">
            <div>
              <p class="eyebrow">Tuition</p>
              <p>¥300,000</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="eyebrow">Accommodation</p>
              <p>¥120,000</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="eyebrow">Food and local transportation</p>
              <p>¥150,000 estimated</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="eyebrow">Outreach</p>
              <p>Not applicable</p>
            </div>
            <div class="surface-accent rounded-md p-lg">
              <p class="eyebrow">Estimated total</p>
              <p><strong>¥570,000</strong></p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>

      <div class="container-narrow" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
        <p class="text-soft">
          Tuition includes lectures, speaker and teacher-related transport, speaker and teacher-related
          food and accommodation, and administrative costs. Accommodation includes wifi, utilities,
          and shared household consumables.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-paper">
    <div class="container container-narrow center stack">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Next Step</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Interested in DBS?</h2>
        <p class="lead mx-auto">
          If you are considering DBS, wondering whether it may be the right next step after DTS,
          or wanting to grow more deeply in Scripture, we would love to help you explore further.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="btn-group" style="justify-content: center;">
        <button type="button" class="btn-primary open-hub-trigger">Ask AI</button>
        <a href="/en/apply" class="btn-secondary">Apply</a>
      </div>

      <div class="btn-group" style="justify-content: center;">
        <a href="/en/contact" class="btn-text">Contact</a>
        <a
          href="https://guide.ywamsendai.org/en"
          class="btn-text"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          Visit Handbook
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>